review_blob: 16 oz can. Pours clear golden with medium thick white head. Nose of peaches and cream oatmeal. Taste is of intense peach balanced by bitter hop. Good summer beer.

12 oz can. Pours a finger of head on a clear straw body. The aroma is lots of mango. Nice. The taste is a bit of a clash between the mango sweetness and the pine bitterness. The texture is crisp. The aroma is nice, but Im not a big fan of the flavor.
12 oz bottle. Clear golden with a thin rocky white head. The aroma is very grapefruity and earthy-bitter. The flavor is moderately bitter but hugely pithy and citrus-twangy grapefruit flavors.

12 oz bottle. Pours a mostly clear amber color with a moderate off-white head on there. Nose has a lot of citrus and fruit notes to it, and is very hop forward. Taste is slightly bitter, but fresh and very drinkable. Decent brew.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Tropical IPA

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. Pours clear orange-gold with a thin beige head, good retention. Aromas of pin e resin, tangerine, grapefruit, and biscuit. Light body, velvety, good carbonation, lightly dry. Mildly sweet, mild bitter finish. Enjoyably citrusy and easy to drink.
12 oz can. Strong vanilla aromatics off the glass. First on the palate is the vanilla but fades fast into the roasted malt flavors of coffee with slight hints of chocolate to finish.

12 oz bottle. Pour is very hazy lemon-flesh yellow with a small white head. Aroma is sweet rock candy-malt, faint lemon notes, and light floral notes. Flavor is faintly tart with hints of lemon, light topical fruit notes, faint floral hops, and a slightly salty finish.

Pours a hazy, very light orange with a thin white head. A nice amount of carbonation. Smells of lemon, straw and yeast/bread. A wonderful ready taste in this cream ale. This taste leaves me wanting more. There is a slight citrus/ lemon hint. I could drink many of these. One of the best cream ales Ive had.

12 oz can. Hazy, burnt orange colored beer with a frothy, white head. Aromas of grassy hops. Tastes of grassy/floral hops, some toffee, and toasted malt. Slightly creamy mouthfeel. Bittersweet in the finish with some grapefruit/citrus notes. Hoppier than expected, more like an IPA than a cream ale in my opinion.

12 oz bottle. Pours black with a full bubbly natural tan head. Aromas of coffee, minerals, and roasted malts. Flavors of chocolate, dark caramel , acidic coffee, and mild roasted malts. Nicely balanced. Smooth and very good!
16 oz can. Pours out as a hazy orange with a nice creamy white nitro head. Aroma is mildly floral. Taste is sweet pale malt, wheat bread dough, some orange zest and only a hint of hop bitterness.

12 oz bottle, hazy orange pour with white head, aroma brought notes of grass, earth, pine, hints of orange, lemon, slight fruity notes into bready notes. Taste is a mix of spice, grass, orange peel into a bit of earth, biscuity/bready notes, hints of grain, finishing spicy, dry, slightly bitter.
12 oz can. Pours a clear golden color. Large white head with some lacing. Strong aroma of coffee grounds. It starts with a vanilla sugary taste then turns to coffee and coffee grounds.
12 oz bottle. Pours clear copper gold with a very thin head. Taste like a honeydew melon. Slightly malty. Light body and low carbonation. This is just not that good!

12 oz bottle. Pours black with a tan head. Rich coffee, cocoa, roasted malt, caramel and resinous hop aroma. Espresso, dark chocolate, cocoa, roasted malt, caramel, toast and hop flavors. Coffee and chocolate finish.
12 oz bottle. Pours a jet black with brown head that disappears quickly. Aroma is blueberry pancakes with maple syrup. Taste is the same with an added touch of coffee. I would not buy again.

12 oz bottle. A slightly hazy red beer with a huge pinkish head. The aroma has strong notes of strawberries, which is smelled far from the glass. The flavor is sweet with strong notes of berries to start off with, leading to a dry lightly tart finish. Not a fan.

22oz bottle. Pours black with small light brown head. Aroma is roasted chocolate malt and bourbon. Chocolate flavor with plenty of roasty notes and some bourbon character. Medium-bodied with lingering roasty and bourbon finish. Just ok.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Wild Turkey Bourbon Barrel Stout

review_blob: 12 oz can. Super hazy yellow-orange with a bubbly off-white head. Aroma of flowers, tropical fruit, wheat, citrus, and white wine. Taste is fruity flowery and sweet-tart. Light-medium bodied, crisp, and a little dry. Full of flavor; quite nice.

12 oz can. Dark brown pour with limited head. Aroma was strong vanilla and cinnamon, but also had light bourbon, chocolate and coffee. Taste was little bit stronger on vanilla and cinnamon, but overall nicely balanced.
beer_name: Tallgrass Vanilla Bean Buffalo Sweat - Bourbon Barrel & Cinnamon

review_blob: 16 oz can. Pours nearly black with a beige head that lasts. Aroma is mostly vanilla, some chocolate some roasted malts. Milky sweet stout with a hint of chocolate and lots of vanilla.

12 oz bottle. Hazy deep hay yellow liquid with minimal white head. Aroma of passion fruit, grain, lemon and bread. Taste is light sweet and light sour with notes of lemon, passion fruit and grain. Medium bodied with medium carbonation. Very tart.
16 oz can. Clear pale color with tiny head. Light aroma of malt. Taste is medium bitter with dry finish. Easy to drink, well balanced. Enjoyable.
beer_name: Toppling Goliath Dorothys New World Lager

review_blob: 16 oz can. Pours an opaque dark brown almost black color with khaki colored head. Chocolate, oats, and some roast on the nose; follows onto the palate. Full bodied, yet very smooth. Finishes with chocolate. Another good offering from TG!
12 oz can pours black with a brown head. Aroma of coffee, whiskey, oak, vanilla and malts. Taste is chocolate, bourbon, vanilla, coffee and it is very smooth.
12 oz. bottle. Pours black with a brief tan head. Taste of roasted coffee with a bit of sweetness. Dry finish with a bitter coffee aftertaste.
750 ml bottle. Nice dark pour with beige head. Roasted malt aroma with nice oak balance. Not real heavy on the tongue. Smooth with nice oak undertones.

12 oz bottle. Pours deep black with a very small tan head. Aroma hits you with big notes of chocolate, bourbon and coffee. Very nice thick, but not too thick mouthfeel. Taste of slight bourbon notes of roasted malts, chocolate and coffee. Overall one of the best beers I have ever had!
Bottle. Hazy pale golden beer with a very big off-white head. Peach and apricot aroma, fruity, malty, sweet. Peach flavor, apricot, orange notes. Not much more than the fruits.
beer_name: R.J. Rockers Son of a Peach Wheat Ale

review_blob: 12 oz can. Pours a bright orange with a nice off white head. Lots of citrus, pine and grapefruit in the nose. Flavor is bitter, with medium sweetness. Some citrus, some citrus zest, fair amount of wheat notes. Light, crisp bodied, finishes bitter.
12 oz bottle. Pours black with small dark brown highlights and nice medium brown head. Creamy, low carbonation, and good lacing. Taste is chocolate, some coffee. Very good beer.
22 oz bottle. Pours dark brown with off white head. Aroma is sweet, peanut butter, roasty. Taste is sweet, chocolate, peanut butter. Kinda tastes like a dark chocolate nutty bar. I like it though
beer_name: 4 Hands Peanut Butter Chocolate Milk Stout

review_blob: Bottle. Deep red color with medium white head. Aroma of burnt wood, caramel, spice, rum. Interesting. In flavor rum, dates, caramel and some unusual, but not unpleasant bitterness. Rum is also present in aftertaste. I like this beer, would buy again.
12 oz Can. Pours a dark almost black with a tan head. Huge chocolate aroma, some cream and coffee. Taste is lots of dark chocolate, dark chocolate bitterness too.

Bottle. Cloudy pale yellow color, big white head. Medium body, average to high carbonation. Aroma of citrus, coriander, malts. Taste is very yeasty, malty with nice banana touch, coriander and citrus.
Bottle. Cloudy pale yellow color with aroma of coriander, lemon, and yeast. Lemongrass, orange, coriander, and yeast flavor.
Pours a clear yellow with medium head. Very smooth with a good taste of malt and honey. Another good beer from New Glarus.
12oz bottle. Mild fruit in the aroma. Sweet and tart malt and cherry with a tapering and watery finish. Not bad, but not one I would gravitate towards again.
Bottle. Dark pour with a light beige head. Smoky aroma with coffee and chocolate. Roasted bitter hoppy taste with coffee finish.
Dark black with a tan head. Aroma of chocolate and nuts. Taste of bitter dark chocolate, coffee and a nutty aftertaste.
This brew is silky smooth and has a generous tan head.The taste is chocolaty, creamy, and rich with some touches of coffee.
750 ml bottle. Light brown with a thick white head. Aroma is roasted cocoa and a bit of spice Flavor is roasted cocoa with a bit of bitterness and a surprisingly clean finish.

On tap at Revolution Tap Room. Pour is close to black with some slight red tinting, small off-white head. Aroma is of milk chocolate with a huge amount of bourbon/oak. Slight cream/roast. Flavor is much like the aroma with a sweet and roasted front but finishes with bourbon. This is now my favorite beer, I cannot get enough of it!
beer_name: Revolution Barrel Aged Mad Cow Milk Stout

review_blob: The brew was a crisp, light straw color with a slight haze to it. Like most flavored beers, the pomegranate was fairly light, but surprisingly pleasant. Could see myself drinking this on a very hot day, very refreshing.
beer_name: Fort Collins Major Toms Pomegranate Wheat

review_blob: Draft at Beer Market. Huge aroma of blueberry muffins, jet black with minimal head. Surprisingly not as much blueberry when tasted. Flavors of chocolate, roasted malt with subtle blueberry. Very surprised!

Pour was deep dark with a slightly dark tan head. Aroma was strong with chocolate, light caramel, and some bread characters. Body was medium to full with a smooth oat character along with some more well blended chocolate malt and a nice caramel finish.
beer_name: Tyranena Down Dirty Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Beautiful dark black motor oil look out of can. Frothy tan head. Aromas of roast, chocolate, black coffee. Taste is same. Sweet malt, bitter coffee, chocolate bitter finish. Lively carbonation slick, creamy mouthfeel. Amazing stout!
Pours near black with thin beige head. Has the aroma of roasted coffee beans and cocoa. Taste is coffee, chocolate, rotated malt, smoke and a hint of bourbon. Pretty good stout.
Bottle. Pours a dark brown watery looking color. Taste is kind of artificial sweet with some banana, clove and cinnamon. Will not purchase again
Pours a dark brown with a lingering tan foam head with some lacing. Has a strong sweet chocolate aroma. Flavor is chocolate and some coffee. I really like this beer. Very balanced.
